Wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Halve, peel, and cut @onion{1} into 1/2-inch-thick wedges. Using the tip of a #spoon{}, remove and discard black gills from undersides of @portobello mushrooms{2}; cut into 1/2-inch-thick strips.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss together @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%ounce}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}, juice from half the lemon, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch} until thoroughly combined (for 4 servings, use 1 tsp sugar and juice from whole lemon). Refrigerate until ready to use.

Open and drain tofu, then press out excess water with #paper towels{} and cut into 3/4-inch cubes, or open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{}, preferably #nonstick{}, over medium-high heat. Using a #spatula{}, arrange into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tofu is browned all over, ~{3-4%minutes}, or until chicken is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{}; wipe out pan.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add another large drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} and mushrooms to pan. Season with half the @shawarma spice blend{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings), a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Reduce heat to medium low and cover. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and tender, ~{3-4%minutes} (you may need to cook in batches for 4).

Use pan used for tofu or chicken here.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @yogurt{2%tablespoon}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, and as much lemon zest as you like. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Toast @pitas{2} until golden brown, then cut into quarters.

Divide veggies, @Sabra Classic Hummus{4%tablespoon}, salad, and pitas between plates in separate sections. Serve with white sauce on the side.

> Enjoy with your favorite hot sauce if you like things spicy!